io.orchestrate.client
Class KvStoreOperation

java.lang.Object
  io.orchestrate.client.KvStoreOperation

public final class KvStoreOperation
extends java.lang.Object

Store an object by key to the Orchestrate.io service.

Usage: 

 MyObject obj = new MyObject(...);
 KvStoreOperation kvStoreOp = new KvStoreOperation("myCollection", "someKey", obj);
 Future<KvMetadata> futureResult = client.execute(kvStoreOp);
 KvMetadata result = futureResult.get();
 System.out.println(metadata.getRef());

See Also:
http://java.orchestrate.io/querying/#store-data

KvStoreOperation

public KvStoreOperation(java.lang.String collection,
                        java.lang.String key,
                        java.lang.Object value,
                        boolean ifAbsent)
Create a new KvStoreOperation to put the specified value in the collection with the key.

When ifAbsent is true this operation succeeds if and only if an object with this key does not already exist.

Parameters:
collection - The collection to store the key to.
key - The key for the object.
value - The value to store.
ifAbsent - If true the operation will only succeed if the key does not already exist.

KvStoreOperation

public KvStoreOperation(java.lang.String collection,
                        java.lang.String key,
                        java.lang.Object value,
                        KvMetadata metadata)
Create a new KvStoreOperation to put the specified value in the collection with the key.

This operation succeeds if and only if the ref from the metadata matches the current ref stored.

Parameters:
collection - The collection to store the key to.
key - The key for the object.
value - The value to store.
metadata - The metadata whose ref must match the current stored ref for the operation to succeed.
